The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Unions and the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions will constitute a strike commission on Friday to coordinate Monday’s strike that will last indefinitely.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday - the day the final vote on the public health law will be held - the work stoppage will begin.
This action will certainly cause great difficulties in transport, since rail transit will be completely halted and until 13 hours workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike.
In the afternoon of Friday, the League Unions will report on the details of their strike on Monday, which they will hold jointly with the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions.
Also will be constituted the strike commission of the LIGA and the National Union of Drivers who will coordinate the actions of Monday.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday the participating unions will strike indefinitely, if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means, that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the law on public health - did not inform about the date of the end of the strike initiated.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their call for a strike.
Instead, if the law is passed, the strike commissions will meet and decide on the future.
On the basis of Monday’s agenda of the National Assembly, it is also possible that the public health law will only be voted on in the very early hours of the night, or at best around midnight.
As a result of the strike that will begin on Monday, there will be significant difficulties in transport: indefinite work will be stopped on the railways, in the morning a part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the intercity transport of buses of the companies Volán may be stopped.
At the same time, in many parts of the country, half of the roads will be closed.
Numerous unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League’s website.
Some unions announced their strike indefinitely, others indefinitely.
Until Thursday afternoon, the State Railways and the Free Trade Union of Rail Workers (SLTF) could not reach an agreement even on the minimum services, although, as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people travel on the trains.
According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day to 13 hours will be on strike workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company, Budapest Airports from 7 to 9 a.m., will hold a four-hour strike the LIG Unions of the Electrical and Thermal Energy Industry, the Educational Unions 2 called a 2-hour strike and the Democratic Union.
The Hungarian Association of Physicians will strike nationally at alternate times and the Democratic Union of Health and Social Sector Workers (SDTSSS) that are part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum, will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is for the government to withdraw its proposal on public health reform and submit a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new form of pension calculation that will come into force next year.
The third is that they ensure, even before 2010, for the case of advanced pensions the possibility that the occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Union of Railway Workers (SLTF), which is part of the League Trade Unions, does not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transportation on the railway sidelines and expect another proposal.
Political Capital[b1]: The Hungarian Guard increases the risk in the country
According to the Risk Analysis Division of the Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed in August this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, has increased from several points of view the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In the company's "risk warning" it is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard the greatest political risk is constituted by the fact that "with the aggravation of the existing ethnic tensions between the Roma and non-Roma population of Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic clashes may occur".
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is probably the provocation of an event of this nature - added the representative of the research institute.
They affirmed that all this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate of the Roma problem to the representatives of the radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the discrepancies between Roma and Hungarians".
This aggravates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, "deteriorated significantly the image of Hungary abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country."
They remind us that: from the autumn of 2006 the reorganization of the radical and far-right groups in Hungary received increasing publicity and impetus, and that since the summer of 2007 numerous organizations have been established in the country that define themselves as "national self-defense associations".
