600,000 people failed to change their driver’s license
Six hundred thousand drivers were passed the date and therefore did not manage to change their old driver's license whose validity ends at the end of the year.
Today is the last day when people can request the change so that officials will give them time until the end of the year to issue the new card.
However, the Ministry does not fear that after the New Year hundreds of thousands of drivers will find themselves on the roads without a valid driver’s license.
According to traffic, the license has not been changed mainly by those who no longer even want to drive.
While in the villages they announce a rapid decline in the change of license, the offices of the metropolis are full of applications and interest in the new license has increased.
The City Council estimates about 2,000 customers daily.
In the queues wait half an hour.
In Prague, around 140,000 drivers have not yet been issued with the new driver's license.
The issuance of a new card lasts twenty days.
However, it is possible to request the issuance of the card in a shorter period of five days.
But in that case the driver must pay five hundred crowns.
Drivers who must change their driver’s license and do not reach until the end of the year, but will take to the roads without a valid license will risk a fine from January.
The offender will pay a maximum of two thousand crowns.
The police can fix the infraction with a warning.
In the event of an administrative infraction, the fine will amount to 2,500 kroner.
According to the above information, a person who does not go anywhere could receive a fine.
They could presumably pay up to 30,000 crowns.
The Ministry appealed to the offices for moderate fines of a thousand crowns, at most.
According to the spokesperson of the transport ministry, Karel Hanzelka, the fines of a thousand crowns do not threaten anyone.
According to him, the driver’s license is a document in which people can decide whether or not they want it.
It is not the identity card that every person must have valid.
People who don’t want to drive should hand over their driver’s license.
Just bring it or send it by registered mail to the municipal offices.
At the end of the year, the licenses issued during the years 1964 and 1993 cease to be valid.
However, drivers will have to gradually change the other types of driving licenses.
People with the document from 1994 to 2000 have up to three years to change it.
The validity of the card that was issued between 2001 and 2004 ends in December 2013.
