The Congress approves the transposition of the MIFID, which entered into force 1 November
Parallel to its parliamentary procedure, which ended today with the vote by Congress of the amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the Government has submitted to a public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the aim that both enter into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the effort made by deputies and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulations in order to guarantee the protection of investors and to regulate in detail the activity of the entities so that the markets function efficiently.
The MIFID, which amends the Securities Market Law, involves the modernization of financial markets, while reinforcing investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and encouraging cooperation between the different supervisors of the European Union.
The new rules will allow financial advisory services to be provided to specialist firms as well as to natural or legal persons and create a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory firms (FIAs), which join securities companies, securities agencies and holding companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of operations on financial instruments, so that the regulated secondary markets are joined by multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with the current exchange managers.
The Act also obliges investment firms to disclose on the market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a record of all the transactions they carry out, to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In its passage through the Congressional Economic Commission, several modifications were incorporated, among which it highlights that securitised debts are considered as a "complex" financial instrument given their high danger to the investor, which has been demonstrated with what happened with the debt of U.S. high-risk mortgages (subprime).
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that can be performed by graduates in Economics and Business 30 years after the royal decree that delimits the professional functions reserved for economists was approved in 1977.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the mediator, who will work for a third party, will not require authorization from the CNMV and will be able to provide its services of marketing products and attracting customers to different investment companies at the same time.
Harmonized CPI rises five-tenths in November to 4.1%
This indicator, which then serves Eurostat to incorporate it into the calculation of the inflation index in the European Union, provides an advance of how prices in Spain evolved during the month of November.
