What insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in case of possible accidents, is an important expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, age of the license, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among others.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we must be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is materialized in an insurance contract, which states that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for being responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a loss.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, age of the card, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use given to it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the greater the likelihood of an accident, the higher the fee to be paid.
It is for this reason that both those over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as the statistics reflect that they have a lower accident rate due to their prudence.
Also, using the counts, companies have come to the conclusion that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use that is given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and with it the probability of having some type of mishap.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when establishing the premium price.
For this reason, the driver must study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
We will expose here the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that this, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 find themselves with various disadvantages when it comes to taking out insurance at an affordable price, such as reduced driving experience and seniority of the license.
Although the ideal to be well insured is an all-risk insurance, there are other more economical options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for an all-risk franchise, so that they get the coverages of an all-risk insurance but at a more feasible price.
This kind of agreement would mean that the customer would pay a part of the amount of the loss.
"The part of the amount of the loss that the customer contributes will be pre-established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," specifies Luis Noguera, head of Spain of First Europa, online insurance broker.
Another option is an extended third-party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection against damage caused to third parties, but not against those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
One piece of advice.
If you are under 25, try to be careful and avoid claims as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, being able to reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate owned by the company.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on that base fee.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year, it can afford to increase the bonuses," explains Noguera.
After 25 years, it is easier for drivers to take out insurance, since the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, the most recommended is to hire a franchised all-risk.
"Normally, young people cannot make use of the experience previously acquired when it comes to utilising themselves in an accident, and even when it comes to driving," says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the rookie' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable to negotiate full-risk insurance, as long as your economic situation allows it, of course.
On the other hand, marriages with children are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest accident rate, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be an all-risk one with a franchise (this can be 300 euros), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of life of the vehicle.
“They carry out a more relaxed driving and have a greater purchasing power to afford to assume a greater amount of franchise,” said Luis Noguera.
For retirees it is advisable to have an all-risk insurance with a franchise (being this one of 150 euros), or one to third parties extended when you have a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in case of possible accidents, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to adequately study the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
