The Best Actor Award went to Viggo Mortensen for his role as a driver for a head of the Russian London Mafia in David Cronenberg's film Eastern Promises.
Ray Winstone, who has a reputation for playing hard, received the Richard Jarris Award for his contribution to British cinema.
