A cell of eight militants made up of foreign residents was planning an attack on an oil facility in the eastern province, the television report said.
Saudi Arabia created a 35,000-strong force to protect the Abqaiq facility, the world’s largest oil plant, after a failed al-Qaeda attack in 2006.
The report, citing a statement from the Saudi Interior Minister, said 18 of those arrested belong to a cell led by a “missile launch expert” who has entered the country.
