In movies like "The Hunting Party" there are also these demons but they show how hard it is to be good.
The problem lies not only in the genre of war movies in the Balkans.
Recently a newspaper published that all films about Iraq produced in Hollywood are fiasco.
It can also be added that there has never been a good film about South Africa.
There’s almost always a rule: when a star gets into a crisis region or minefields, then something like “Rangoon” with Patricia Arguette, “Across All Borders” with Angelina Jolie or “Bloody Diamonds” with Leonardo DiCaprio appears.
