He referred to the decision of the Sports Federation (Sportbund) expected in early December, on Munich’s request for the 2028 Winter Olympics.
“This preference means for us that in this period of time, which until now we thought we would have until 2028, from a realistic point of view we will not have any opportunity.”
This dream, however, did not end forever, said von Beust.
The Hamburg Sports Federation (HSB) regrets von Beut’s remarks.
This gives the impression that in the next 25 years Hamburg does not want to apply for the Olympics.
"It's too soon to let the opportunity be taken away if at this point the plans are ruined," Günter Ploß, the director of HSB, said on Wednesday.
A waiver of the request is contradictory to the statement of the head of the senate made at a reception on the occasion of the general meeting of the German Public Sport Federation of Higher Schools (adh).
There von Beust designated the Hamburg application for Universities 2015 not as "a substitute" for the Olympic Games in Hamburg.
Only last week the Higher School Sports Federation named Hamburg as an application candidate.
