It's not the wooden boxes.
Whoever relates the terms Sweden and wooden box, thinks of Ikea, but does not think of Andy Warhol.
Or is it?
Currently the wooden boxes produced in Sweden are like the shadow that weighs on Warhol’s list of works.
Most of the ninety-four "type" Gloss-Boxes on this list are fake.
After a few months ago the Swedish newspaper "Expressen" cast doubt on the authenticity of Andy Warhol's 1968 Brillo-Boxes, the Moderna Museet Museum in Stockholm conducted internal investigations and came to disappointing conclusions: the six "Brillo-Boxes", which the former director of the Pontus Hultén museum in Stockholm also gave to the international museum of Moderna Museet, are fake, and almost one of them.
Prehistory is too complicated with a confusing relationship between artistic and sponsored productions.
In 1964 Warhol created in New York his first "Brillo-Boxes", he painted the wooden boxes of red, blue and white, with the same sample that had cartons of soap powder "Brillo".
According to Warhol, at the 1968 exhibition of his works at the Moderna Museet hundreds of Gloss-cardboard boxes were exhibited. These were not made by Warhol (because of the expenses), but were brought directly from the "Brillo" cardboard factory.
These were not works of art, but specimens (which were only objects) on display.
In the same year, 1968, Warhol allowed the production of glossy wooden boxes in Sweden, but they were not exhibited at the Modern Museet.
Witnesses of those times now speak of almost fifteen boxes, which at that time entered the history of art and auctions as originals of the "Brillo-Boxes" of "type Stockholm" authorized by Andy Warhol.
At auctions some of them were bought for more than $100,000.
The problem is that after the famous director of the Pontus Hultén museum made false statements that in 1968 in Sweden almost a hundred of the wooden boxes that Warhol left to him were produced and exposed.
But in reality, 105 boxes were produced in the same year 1990 in Malmö for Hultén and for the exhibition in St. Petersburg.
At this time Warhol had already died for 3 years.
Lars Byström, the chief curator of the Moderna Museet museum, investigated six Brillo-Boxes owned by the museum and also three of the Swedish private property that were manufactured in 1968 in Stockholm. First they printed and grinded their tight silvers and then they painted them in oil with the brush.
On the contrary, the structure of the copies of the year 1990 shows that the paint was applied with a roller without directly printing the tightened silvers. In addition, it is not oil paint, but acrylic paint.
“These boxes have not been authorized by the artist and must be removed from the official Andy Warhol Brillo-Boxes list,” says Lars Nittve, director of the Moderna Museet museum, adding that if the Andy Warhol Art Authentication Commission in New York fails to reach any conclusion, the Moderna Museet museum will classify these six boxes as the copies/objects of the exhibition.
Already in July the Authentication Commission formally announced that it accepts these "serious accusations" in which they are boxes of soap powder.
But from that moment on everything remained in absolute silence.
Rebel soldiers surrender in Manila.
In the Philippines, rebel soldiers who had entrenched themselves in a hotel in Manila and demanded the overthrow of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo have surrendered.
Chief Antonio Trillanes, who blames the president for corruption and election fraud, told a reporter he could not answer for spilling blood.
Soldiers loyal to the government had raided the hotel using tear gas.
Nearly two hundred soldiers had been entrenching themselves in the building for a few hours.
Nearly half of them, including Trillanes, were on trial Thursday for attempting a 2003 coup that ended in failure.
He took advantage of the negotiations, to suddenly be able to deposit with about 30 supporters.
Evidently the military police officers who were to watch him had passed into their ranks and followed his mutiny.
They entered the "Peninsula" hotel and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Government troops blockaded the neighborhood around the Hotel Noble.
The president called for an urgent session of the Security Cabinet.
Norberto Gonzales, the National Security Advisor, condemned the behavior of the soldiers.
“People are fed up,” Trillanes said.
“We call on people to come to our ranks.”
General Danilo Lim, who previously led the elite Scout Reangers troop, said the other military troops would soon want to follow the march.
Major government critics called for a major demonstration against the president on Thursday.
For months his government has been blamed for corruption.
In 2003 the financial district in Manila was a site that attracted all the attention for the mutiny that was attempted against Arroyo.
The uprising failed after about 24 hours because the army wanted to participate.
Since 1986 in the Philippines there have been at least seven attempted coups against the democratically elected government.
United Internet will be Versatel’s largest shareholder.
United Internet secured more than 20 percent of the shares in telecommunications company Versatel.
On Wednesday, the company reported that the average price for a share is 14.46 euros.
It has only 20.05 percent of the share capital.
There was much speculation about the company’s absorption.
There are also options to further increase the financial part at Versatel.
United Internet reported that with this step it wants to accelerate the consolidation of the German DSL (Digital Subscriber Line) market.
On Wednesday they already made assumptions about entering the business, after bank Brendenberg increased its stake in the Duesseldorf network operator by 5 percent to 15.1 percent.
In the financial market this means that the financial institution holds equity securities for a third-party partner.
United Internet already on the previous day engaged with almost 10 percent the telecommunications company Drillisch.
Drillisch in the capital increase measure placed 17.4 million of the new shares that have a value of 106.4 million euros.
United Internet has purchased 5.15 million shares of them for <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>31.4 million.
In addition, the companies began negotiations on DSL-product marketing cooperations.
“We strengthen our collaboration,” the United Internet spokesperson explained.
The two companies founded a joint venture MSP, to acquire competitor Freenet.
On Thursday, United Internet reported that in the beginning, the two companies want to be happy with the ten percent stake in Freenet and do not make use of their right, that is, they involve 18.49 percent of Freenet.
That meant that both companies retained all the options, especially the participation in the Freenet public limited company.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet over a strategic partnership ended in mid-November.
This “game” with Freenet that will last for many months and is not very understandable is part of the consolidation of the German Telecom market.
At the end of the third quarter, Freenet had 2.9 million customers with a mobile phone contract and 1.27 million with a DSL contract or a full contract.
Until now, the holding company of United Internet and Drillisch held a direct 6.01% stake in Freenet.
Then they had agreed that Drillisch would get the other four percent.
The right to buy 18.49 percent of investment company Vatas was already agreed in August.
